<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 16 at 8:27AM CDT until April 16 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 845 AM CDT
FOR NORTHERN CALHOUN COUNTY...
At 827 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Ellisville, or
9 miles north of Hampton, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Fordyce...                        Thornton...
Harlow...                         Highland Industrial Park...
Chambersville...                  Hopeville...
Woodberry...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
